01/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) President Milorad Dodik called the entity's parliament on Thursday (March 31st) to convene at a special session to debate the validity of the BiH Court and Prosecutor's Office.
Dodik maintains these institutions are unconstitutional and RS should organise a referendum on whether they should exist in the present form.
(RTRS, Nezavisne Novine, Fena, BHRT - 31/03/11)
